---
By: Sivananda
Locus:
  Page: 504
  Verse: 2
Tags:
  - Worry
---
Worry kills a man. It destroys his hope of life. It is a canker or cancer
that slowly eats away at man. It wears you out. Do not worry over the past.
...Do not worry about things which are likely to happen; so often they
really do not.
